                            <comment id="18454" author="springboy" created="Fri, 7 Jul 2006 04:50:49 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Hi Matthew&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Ack, you got me man &lt;img class=&quot;emoticon&quot; src=&quot;https://jira.spring.io/images/icons/emoticons/smile.png&quot; height=&quot;16&quot; width=&quot;16&quot; align=&quot;absmiddle&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; border=&quot;0&quot;/&gt; Thans for spotting this; I&apos;ll try explain what you are seeing.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;As part of the big push for Spring 2.0, I significantly &apos;refactored&apos; the existing reference documentation. The documentation is now (to my mind) much cleaner, with better explanations of key topics. It will however break any existing links that folks have bookmarked. I thought this would be ok because the overall improvement in the documentation (to my mind) outweighs the potential link breakage. After Spring 2.0 final you can be guaranteed that sections and thus links will not be moved about arbitrarily.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The issues you are having can be explained thusly...&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The two chapter 2s is due to the fact that the &apos;old&apos; chaoter 2 file (&apos;Background&apos;) has been pulled into a sidebar in the overview chapter. I didn&apos;t feel that the name check of Martin Fowler quite merited a whole chapter for what was essentially just a link to his bliki. I will remove the spurious artefact file shortly.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;http://static.springframework.org/spring/docs/2.0.x/reference/introduction.html#background-ioc&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;http://static.springframework.org/spring/docs/2.0.x/reference/introduction.html#background-ioc&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The section entitled &apos;4.16. Setting a bean property or constructor arg from a field value&apos; has been folded into the XML configuration chapter, because using the &amp;lt;util:constant/&amp;gt; or &amp;lt;util:property-path/&amp;gt; elements are now the recommended ways of doing this. See this link...&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;http://static.springframework.org/spring/docs/2.0.x/reference/xsd-config.html#d0e28225&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;http://static.springframework.org/spring/docs/2.0.x/reference/xsd-config.html#d0e28225&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Finally the section entitled &apos;Glue code and the evil singleton&apos; can be found at this new link (see below); the TOC that I am looking at on the public website has it as section 3.9, and it is indeed section 3.9 in the actual chapter. I guess you must be lloking at an old version( ?).&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;http://static.springframework.org/spring/docs/2.0.x/reference/beans.html#d0e5219&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;http://static.springframework.org/spring/docs/2.0.x/reference/beans.html#d0e5219&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Cheers&lt;br/&gt;
Rick&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="18457" author="sgarlatm" created="Fri, 7 Jul 2006 06:12:44 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I looked briefly at the documentation in the early chapters and it looked like a very nice improvement over the old stuff.  Nice work &lt;img class=&quot;emoticon&quot; src=&quot;https://jira.spring.io/images/icons/emoticons/smile.png&quot; height=&quot;16&quot; width=&quot;16&quot; align=&quot;absmiddle&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; border=&quot;0&quot;/&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
